13:
You're seriously telling me you're
surrounded by all these beautiful
women, and NONE of them have
caught your eye?
17:
I mean, some of them are pretty
eye-catching, but...
21:
Aha! So you're not completely blind.
All right, now let me guess... Is it
Stella?
29:
Yeah, I bet you want someone with
a more... MATURE body type!
35: That's not it! Ugh, will you just—
39:
Aren't we supposed to be quiet in
the library?
42: Stella's going to get mad at you.
45:
Alk's type, huh? What would that be
like?
54:
I guess so. It's kinda like reading a
science-fiction novel. You know,
exploring the unknown.
56:
Although, I gotta say, I'd be more
interested to know what Stella's type
is.
60:
Ohhh, good point. She's so innocent.
Has she even had her first crush yet?
65:
Yeah, I can't really picture it... I just
hope it doesn't end up being
someone like you, Sho...
69:
What are you, her DAD?! And why
the diss, man?! I thought we were
friends!
72:
Hey, you... don't just sit there
grinning. What about you, Nova? Got
a type?
77: Me? Of course I do. I like cuties.
90:
Ah, speaking of which, did you reply
to that love letter yet?
100:
Huh? Wait, was that supposed to be
a secret?
104:
I mean, it's not a big deal,
but—anyway, would you look at the
time! Gotta get to work!
108:
Hmmm... I sense the Oudo of a
coward.
113:
Sho's been helping retrieve drifters
from the Kaleidoscope. A lot of them
are coming from Shibuya lately.
116:
Many of them ended up with
powers, but suddenly finding
yourself in a dungeon full of
monsters is a little much for some
people.
121:
I see. His powers are perfect then. He
can send them directly to the
surface, out of harm's way.
126:
I've heard some of the rescued
drifters have started calling him the
Flying Prince.
130:
The heck? Is this a comic book or
something?
135:
All right... Just gotta set them down,
nice and gently...
145:
Thanks a million, Shota! Nobody
looks injured either! You're amazing!
149:
Haha, It's no biggie! I barely broke a
sweat.
152:
By the way... That last shift was
bigger than usual, right?
156:
...I'm gonna take one more look
around.
160:
What?! W-wait, if you're going back
in, at least meet up with another
party and—
164: I'll be fine! Back in a flash!
173:
Was that... What ever it was, it came
from this direction!
176:
No... Wh-where is this place? Why
are we here...
184: Ah, aren't you part of Aegis?
187:
...Not that it matters. I'm not gonna
ignore someone in danger. Just
don't get an attitude with—
212:
Wahaha! Leave this to me, young
man!
221:
I won't be able to hold back this foul
beast for long! Now make haste and
get these innocents to safety!
234:
*huff* *puff* Perfect. Get these
people to the exit!
237:
Y-you're not planning on going back
there... are you?
241:
Sorry, but... I don't wanna run away. I
gotta go back and fight!
246:
I'm not the pathetic loser you used
to know!
250:
T-take me with you! I can act as
your guard!
255:
And I can help you retreat when
needed! You can take us both, right?
261:
We'll take the rest of these survivors
back to the surface and call for
backup!
269:
...Yeah. I can fight, so take me with
you!
272: Hehe, that's what I like to hear!
275:
Buckle up! It's gonna be a bumpy
ride!
285:
I'm a thickheaded numbskull who
couldn't read the room if his life
depended on it... However...
288:
I don't think anyone can pity me
anymore!
